{"type":"message","id":"9c7f3a5d","parentId":"c0b092c9","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:21:37.898Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bun is not installed. Let me check if npm/node is available and can be used instead. The project has a `package.json` so we could try with npm. But looking at the `bun.lock` file, it might be Bun-specific.\n\nLet me check if there's a way to install bun or use npm. But actually, before I get too deep into building, let me think about what the user actually wants.\n\n\"Integrate it/ replace the control ui with design and theming from the ui\"\n\nI think the key insight is: the cockpit project has a design system (dark theme with oklch colors, specific component styling). The user wants this design system applied to the workspace's control UI.\n\nThere are two approaches:\n1. **Full replacement**: Build the cockpit and make it the control UI\n2. **Design system extraction**: Extract the CSS/theme from the cockpit and apply it to the existing control UI\n\nGiven that:\n- The cockpit is a full chat app (not a control panel)\n- The control UI is the OpenClaw management interface\n- The cockpit's design is beautiful (dark, oklch-based, modern)\n\nI think the user wants to either:\na) Use the cockpit's design tokens to theme the control UI\nb) Or have the cockpit available as an additional/alternative UI\n\nLet me try a different approach. Since the Control UI supports tweakcn themes, I could extract the cockpit's CSS variables and create a tweakcn-compatible theme. But tweakcn uses a different format...\n\nActually, let me just try to build the project with npm and see what happens. If it builds, we get static files. If the static files can replace the control UI, great. If not, we can still serve them.\n\nWait, I should check if there's an `index.html` in the src directory or if TanStack Start generates it.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_qPQuJxzkEamfqZBBNnjYdoXL","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/asherlewis/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-cockpit && ls src/routes/ 2>/dev/null || ls src/"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi","model":"kimi-for-coding","usage":{"input":276,"output":434,"cacheRead":53760,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54470,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779391285841,"responseId":"msg_ZDwOkfGXkXP5XaSw5B42jDQE"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a1ae617","parentId":"9c7f3a5d","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:21:37.938Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_qPQuJxzkEamfqZBBNnjYdoXL","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"__root.tsx\nimages.tsx\nindex.tsx\nlibrary.tsx\nsettings.tsx\nthread.$id.tsx\nvideos.tsx"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":14,"aggregated":"__root.tsx\nimages.tsx\nindex.tsx\nlibrary.tsx\nsettings.tsx\nthread.$id.tsx\nvideos.tsx","cwd":"/Users/asherlewis/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779391297936}}
{"type":"message","id":"a0243eec","parentId":"5a1ae617","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:21:49.589Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the router and see how TanStack Start is configured. Also, I should look at the index.html situation - TanStack Start typically generates its own HTML shell. Let me see if there's a way to build this to static files.\n\nActually, I think I should focus on what the user wants: to integrate the cockpit into the workspace and replace the control UI with its design/theming. Let me check if we can configure the gateway to serve a different UI or if we can just extract the theme.\n\nLooking at the docs again, the Control UI has an Appearance panel with theme import from tweakcn. The cockpit's design system uses CSS custom properties with oklch colors. We could potentially:\n1. Extract the cockpit's CSS variables into a tweakcn-compatible theme\n2. Build the cockpit as a standalone app and run it\n3. Replace the control-ui dist files with a built cockpit\n\nLet me try approach 3 first since it's the most direct. But TanStack Start apps are SSR-first... Let me check if there's a client-only build option.\n\nActually, looking at the `vite.config.ts` more carefully - it uses `@lovable.dev/vite-tanstack-config` which is a wrapper. The `@cloudflare/vite-plugin` is also included. This is definitely an SSR app.\n\nFor a simpler approach, let me:\n1. Try to extract the cockpit's design system (CSS variables, colors)\n2. Create a theme file that can be imported into the Control UI\n3. Also set up the cockpit to be runnable as a separate dev server\n\nBut wait, maybe the user just wants the cockpit to be the workspace's UI. In that case, we should:\n1. Make sure it can be built/run\n2. Configure the workspace to use it\n\nLet me check if npm install works and try building. But bun is required based on the lockfile...\n\nActually, let me step back. The user said \"replace the control ui with design and theming from the ui\". This is pretty clear - they want the design and theming from the cockpit applied to/replacing the control UI. \n\nGiven the constraints:\n- The control UI is built into OpenClaw and is a Lit app\n- The cockpit is a React/TanStack Start app\n- We can't easily replace one with the other without building\n\nI think the best approach is:\n1. Try to build the cockpit with npm (convert bun.lock if needed)\n2. If it builds, set up a way to serve it (either as static files or via a dev server)\n3. Configure OpenClaw to use it or provide instructions\n\nOR, more practically:\n1. Extract the cockpit's theme/CSS variables\n2. Create a custom theme for the Control UI\n3. Also keep the cockpit as a runnable project in the workspace\n\nLet me check the OpenClaw config to see if there's a `controlUi` section that might let us specify a custom directory.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_011EuLn6kC957kYZLwt8fPYw","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config get gateway.controlUi 2>/dev/null || echo \"No controlUi config or openclaw not running\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi","model":"kimi-for-coding","usage":{"input":496,"output":648,"cacheRead":54016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55160,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779391297938,"responseId":"msg_SLuW6l1lj0mcqdbVkBmkQRNg"}}
