{"type":"message","id":"487030b1","parentId":"9914157e","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:22:10.864Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me take a different approach. Since the gateway isn't running, let me check the docs for config options related to control UI. I already saw from the web fetch that `gateway.controlUi.basePath` exists. Let me check if there's a way to set a custom directory.\n\nActually, looking at the web fetch result more carefully, it says:\n- \"default: `http://<host>:18789/`\"\n- \"optional prefix: set `gateway.controlUi.basePath` (e.g. `/openclaw`)\"\n\nSo `basePath` is just a URL path prefix, not a filesystem path. The Control UI is served from the OpenClaw npm package's `dist/control-ui/` directory.\n\nTo replace it, we'd need to either:\n1. Replace the files in `node_modules/openclaw/dist/control-ui/` (not persistent across updates)\n2. Fork/modify OpenClaw itself\n3. Serve the cockpit separately and proxy/redirect to it\n4. Extract the design system and import it as a theme\n\nGiven the user's request \"replace the control ui with design and theming from the ui\", I think the most practical and maintainable approach is:\n\n**Extract the cockpit's design system and create a tweakcn-compatible theme that can be imported into the Control UI.**\n\nBut actually, looking at the cockpit again - it's a full application (chat interface, settings, etc.). The user might want the cockpit to BE the control UI, not just its theme. Let me re-read the messages:\n\n- \"Did the ui / workspace migration land?\"\n- \"No in .openclaw/workspace/openclaw-cockpit\"\n- \"Integrate it/ replace the control ui with design and theming from the ui\"\n\nSo the user put the cockpit in the workspace and wants it integrated. \"replace the control ui with design and theming from the ui\" could mean:\n1. Use the cockpit's design to replace the control UI's design\n2. OR replace the control UI entirely with the cockpit\n\nGiven that the cockpit is a chat console for API endpoints and the control UI is a management dashboard, they serve different purposes. But the user might want the cockpit as an alternative interface.\n\nI think the best approach is:\n1. Build the cockpit project (or set it up to run)\n2. Extract its design tokens\n3. Create instructions/scripts for using it\n4. Maybe set up a proxy or redirect\n\nBut we can't build without bun... Let me check if we can install bun or use npm.\n\nActually, let me try a more practical approach. Let me:\n1. Check if the cockpit can run with npm instead of bun\n2. Try to install dependencies with npm\n3. See if it builds\n\nOr, I could extract the design system right now and create a theme file that can be imported.\n\nLet me first check if bun can be installed easily on macOS.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_cqEaxh4m67iti6y3BZzhniwL","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash 2>&1 | tail -5","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi","model":"kimi-for-coding","usage":{"input":252,"output":633,"cacheRead":55040,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55925,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779391316880,"responseId":"msg_Q7whhQrYEKZhMXo6RiorxKNG"}}
