{"type":"message","id":"f28b2e83","parentId":"e3d2bbdc","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:28:34.058Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_hlK3TIEDEJnpTgN3YquAxFmu","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        const { cloudflare } = await import(\"@cloudflare/vite-plugin\");\n        const cfOptions = typeof options.cloudflare === \"object\" && options.cloudflare || {\n          viteEnvironment: { name: \"ssr\" }\n        };\n        internalPlugins.push(cloudflare(cfOptions));\n      } catch {\n      }\n    }\n    const { tanstackStart } = await import(\"@tanstack/react-start/plugin/vite\");\n    const tanstackStartDefaults = {\n      importProtection: {\n        behavior: \"error\",\n        client: {\n          files: [\"**/server/**\"],\n          specifiers: [\"server-only\"]\n        }\n      }\n    };\n    const tanstackStartOptions = mergeConfig(tanstackStartDefaults, options.tanstackStart ?? {});\n    internalPlugins.push(tanstackStart(tanstackStartOptions));\n    const viteReact = (await import(\"@vitejs/plugin-react\")).default;\n    internalPlugins.push(viteReact(options.react));\n    if (command === \"serve\") {\n      const hmrGateOpt = options.hmrGate;\n      const enableHmrGate = isSandbox ? hmrGateOpt !== false : !!hmrGateOpt;\n      if (enableHmrGate) {\n        const { hmrGatePlugin } = await import(\"@lovable.dev/vite-plugin-hmr-gate\");\n        const hmrGateOptions = typeof hmrGateOpt === \"object\" ? hmrGateOpt : {};\n        internalPlugins.push(hmrGatePlugin(hmrGateOptions));\n      }\n    }\n    if (command === \"serve\" && isSandbox) {\n      const { devServerBridgePlugin } = await import(\"@lovable.dev/vite-plugin-dev-server-bridge\");\n      internalPlugins.push(devServerBridgePlugin());\n    }\n    if (command === \"serve\" && mode === \"development\") {\n      internalPlugins.push(componentTagger());\n    }\n    let envDefine = {};\n    if (options.envDefine !== false) {\n      const loadedEnv = loadEnv(mode, process.cwd(), \"VITE_\");\n      for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(loadedEnv)) {\n        envDefine[`import.meta.env.${key}`] = JSON.stringify(value);\n      }\n    }\n    let config = {\n      define: envDefine,\n      resolve: {\n        alias: {\n          \"@\": `${process.cwd()}/src`\n        },\n        dedupe: [\n          \"react\",\n          \"react-dom\",\n          \"react/jsx-runtime\",\n          \"react/jsx-dev-runtime\",\n          \"@tanstack/react-query\",\n          \"@tanstack/query-core\"\n        ]\n      },\n      plugins: [...internalPlugins, ...options.plugins ?? []]\n    };\n    if (options.vite) {\n      config = mergeConfig(config, options.vite);\n    }\n    if (isSandbox) {\n      validateConfig(config);\n      config = cleanServerConfig(\n        mergeConfig(config, {\n          server: { host: \"::\", port: 8080, strictPort: true }\n        })\n      );\n    } else {\n      config = mergeConfig({ server: { host: \"::\", port: 8080 } }, config);\n    }\n    if (isSandbox) {\n      return config;\n    }\n    return applyWatchDebounceDefaults(config);\n  };\n}\nexport {\n  defineConfig\n};\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1779391714057}}
{"type":"message","id":"a46d4e8d","parentId":"f28b2e83","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:28:49.764Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the lovable config uses the `@cloudflare/vite-plugin` which outputs `index.js` as the worker entry. The `@tanstack/react-start/plugin/vite` is what handles prerendering, and it expects `server.js` for the preview server.\n\nThe issue is that the Cloudflare plugin renames the output to `index.js` because it's designed for Cloudflare Workers. For prerendering to work, we need the server entry to be `server.js`.\n\nLet me try a different approach. Instead of fighting with the build system, let me:\n\n1. Create a simple post-build script that copies `dist/server/index.js` to `dist/server/server.js` and then re-runs just the prerender step\n2. Or, manually create a static HTML shell that loads the client assets\n\nActually, the simplest approach might be to just use the `vite preview` server. Since the cockpit is meant to be a dev tool, running `bun run preview` would serve it. And for \"replacing the control UI\", we could configure the OpenClaw gateway to proxy to the cockpit preview server.\n\nBut wait - the user said \"design and theming from the ui\". Let me re-read that.\n\n\"Integrate it/ replace the control ui with design and theming from the ui\"\n\nI think the key insight is they want the DESIGN AND THEMING - the visual style, colors, components - to be applied to the workspace's UI. The cockpit itself IS the UI they want.\n\nLet me try a different approach. Since the cockpit is already in the workspace and builds successfully, let me:\n\n1. Create a startup script for the cockpit\n2. Extract the CSS/design tokens into a shareable theme\n3. Document how to use it\n4. Try to create a static version by manually rendering the HTML shell\n\nFor the static version, I can create a simple `index.html` that:\n- Loads the CSS from `dist/client/assets/styles-vtW7et7B.css`\n- Loads the JS chunks\n- Has a `<div id=\"root\"></div>` for React to mount\n\nBut TanStack Start's router needs the HTML to be generated server-side for hydration to work. A purely static HTML might not work correctly.\n\nLet me try yet another approach. I'll use the prerender feature but fix the server.js issue by creating a custom build script.\n\nActually, looking at this more practically, let me:\n1. Build the project\n2. Manually create `dist/server/server.js` that re-exports `index.js`\n3. Then run the build again... but the build will wipe it\n\nOK, I think the best approach is to create a custom build script in package.json:\n\n```json\n\"build:static\": \"vite build && cp dist/server/index.js dist/server/server.js && vite build --prerender\"\n```\n\nBut vite build doesn't have a `--prerender` flag - prerendering is part of the build when configured.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The prerender step runs after the SSR build. It needs the preview server to be available. The preview server looks for `server.js`. If I create `server.js` before the build step completes... no, the build cleans dist/.\n\nWhat if I modify the wrangler.jsonc to use a different main entry? No, that won't help because it's the Vite build output name.\n\nActually, let me check if the Cloudflare vite plugin has an option to change the output file name. Or if I can override the Rollup output config.\n\nActually, the simplest fix: add a custom Vite plugin that copies `index.js` to `server.js` after the build. Let me modify vite.config.ts to include a post-build plugin.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_V2WBVu0dheJRyBf84BKpNoIR","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import { defineConfig } from \"@lovable.dev/vite-tanstack-config\";\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  tanstackStart: {\n    server: { entry: \"server\" },\n    prerender: {\n      enabled: true,\n      autoSubfolderIndex: true,\n      autoStaticPathsDiscovery: true,\n      crawlLinks: true,\n      failOnError: false,\n    },\n  },\n  plugins: [\n    {\n      name: \"copy-server-js\",\n      closeBundle() {\n        const fs = require(\"fs\");\n        const path = require(\"path\");\n        const distServer = path.resolve(process.cwd(), \"dist/server\");\n        const indexPath = path.join(distServer, \"index.js\");\n        const serverPath = path.join(distServer, \"server.js\");\n        if (fs.existsSync(indexPath) && !fs.existsSync(serverPath)) {\n          fs.copyFileSync(indexPath, serverPath);\n          console.log(\"[copy-server-js] Copied index.js -> server.js\");\n        }\n      },\n    },\n  ],\n});\n","path":"/Users/asherlewis/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-cockpit/vite.config.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi","model":"kimi-for-coding","usage":{"input":765,"output":1065,"cacheRead":70656,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72486,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779391714061,"responseId":"msg_xFJNjZ200iBv3mj8nbpBJFSN"}}
